code-

var once = function(fn) {
    let called = false;

    return function(...args) {
        if (!called) {
            called = true;
            return fn(...args);
        }
        return undefined;
    };
};



Once Function
Problem-
Given a function fn
Return a new function that:
- Calls fn only once
- First call → returns result of fn
- Next calls → return undefined

Logic-
- Use a variable to track if function is already called
-Initially → called = false
- On first call:
  -> Execute fn
  -> Set called = true
-On next calls:
 -> Return undefined
